title: [Grawood Farmstead, Field]
description: The untilled soil here at the center of the field is of a lighter hue than that of the rows, having been longer exposed to the air and elements.  It creates a dusty floor for a scattering of tents and booths and manages to grow little more than ragged tufts of grass.
paths: Obvious paths: north, northeast, east, south, southwest, west
room.location: Grawood Farmstead outside of River's Rest
